sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K180014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Composite part, consisting of BBa_K180005 and BBa_K180015, but with BBa_K180005 reading along the reverse strand, and BBa_K180015 reading along the forward strand.
Forms the 'paper' primary plasmid in Team:Southampton's rock-paper-scissors project design.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Richard Wilson, Stephanie Chambers
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: See relevant biobrick component parts (BBa_K180011 and BBa_K180012).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_K180005 reading along reverse strand, and BBa_K180015 reading along the forward strand to ensure the constitutive promoter BBa_J23119 (present in BBa_K180005) has no effect over GFP or RhlI expression in BBa_K180015.
